Methods for DOM selecting:

document.getElementById()
-selects element based on its id

document.getElementsByClassName()
-selects elements based on class name, returns them in a list

document.getElementsByTagName()
-selects elements based on tag name, returns them in a list (node list, not array). Each entry is an object

document.querySelector("#highlight")
-takes a css-style selector
-returns first element that matches

document.querySelectorAll(".bolded")
-takes a css-style selector
-returns all elements that match 

Methods for DOM manipulation:
-document.style
-define css class, toggle it within js
-classList.toggle
-classList.add
-classList.remove
-classList is not an array

.textContent
.innerHTML (includes other tags when copied, recognizes html)